headline: 3 High-Yield Dividend Growth Stocks to Buy in December and Hold for a Decade or Longer
summary: It's been a great couple of years for the stock market.  During this bull run, stock prices have bounded forward much further than earnings from their underlying businesses.  As a result, the average dividend payer in the benchmark index offers a paltry 1.2% yield at recent prices.
